The paper deals with the semantics of functional programming languages, specifically focusing on nondeterministic programs. This suggests that it could belong to the Logic (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL), or Theoretical Computer Science (cs.THEORY) sub-categories. The use of denotational semantics and the focus on continuity and computability also suggest a strong theoretical component, making cs.THEORY a likely category. The use of functional programming languages and the focus on algorithms and data structures suggest cs.PL and cs.SE as likely categories. The use of biorders and the focus on structure preservation suggest cs.LO as a likely category.
